message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper involves the use of deep learning models for image segmentation and volume estimation in medical imaging, specifically for cardiac MRI. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the focus on medical imaging and disease detection suggests that it could belong to cs.MED (Medical Imaging) and cs.NEURON (Computational Neuroscience).
